<h3><code>ui-buttons</code></h3>

<h3>Buttons Component</h3>
<desc>
  The primary "grouping" components, it groups buttons together by wrapping them in the <code>div</code> of class <em>btn-group</em>. This naming convention is consistent with Bootstrap and leverages the CSS that comes with CSS to make everything look right. In a broader fashion, this component is about bringing "together" button widgets (of various types) that contextually are related and allowing them to behave in a coordinated fashion as well as visually to present themselves as a group entity.
</desc>
<desc>
  <note>Note: this component is still a work in progress, feel free to contribute with a PR.</note>
</desc>

<h3>Basics</h3>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{#ui-buttons}}
      {{ui-button title='foo'}}
      {{ui-button title='bar'}}
      {{ui-button title='baz'}}
    {{/ui-buttons}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5 monospace">
  <b>\{{#ui-buttons}}</b><br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='foo'}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='bar'}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='baz'}}<br/>
  <b>\{{/ui-buttons}}</b>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5">
    Illustrates the most basic usage of this component. Basically all you're getting here is some additional bootstrap styling which rounds the corners in a pleasing way.
  </div>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{#ui-buttons howMany=howMany disabled=isDisabled as |group|}}
      {{ui-button title='foo' group=group}}
      {{ui-button title='bar' group=group}}
      {{ui-button title='baz' group=group}}
    {{/ui-buttons}}<br/>
    # registered: {{howMany}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5 monospace">
  <b>\{{#ui-buttons howMany=howMany as |group|}}</b><br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='foo' group=group}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='bar' group=group}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-button title='baz' group=group}}<br/>
  <b>\{{/ui-buttons}}</b><br/>
  # registered: \{{howMany}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5">
    When a button detects its <code>group</code> property has been set then it uses this to register itself
    with the group. Registration allows the <code>ui-buttons</code> component to orchestrate certain things like
    sizing, enablement/disablement, etc.<br/>
    <p class="downer">
      {{ui-toggle-button on='enable the group' off='disable the group' value=isDisabled}}
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{#ui-buttons as |group2|}}
      {{ui-radio-button title='foo' group=group2}}
      {{ui-radio-button title='bar' group=group2}}
      {{ui-radio-button title='baz' group=group2}}
    {{/ui-buttons}}
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5 monospace">
  <b>\{{#ui-buttons as |group2|}}</b><br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-radio-button title='foo' group=group2}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-radio-button title='bar' group=group2}}<br/>
    &nbsp;&nbsp;\{{ui-radio-button title='baz' group=group2}}<br/>
  <b>\{{/ui-buttons}}</b><br/>
  </div>
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-4 col-lg-5">
    Up to now we were just using the regular old <code>ui-button</code> button but more often then not when're grouping buttons we're going to want to use either a <em>radio</em> or <em>checkbox</em> styled button which contains some "state". In the case of a
    radio button, you can see that only one button at a time can be picked.
  </div>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-xs-4 col-sm-3 col-lg-2">
    {{ui-buttons
      type='radio'
